

# GenAI × Private 5G in Industrial Edge Computing — Competitive Landscape

## Executive Summary

The convergence of Generative AI (GenAI) and Private 5G in industrial edge computing is one of the fastest-moving arenas in enterprise technology as of 2025. The competitive field is moderately concentrated at the infrastructure layer — dominated by Ericsson and Nokia who hold record private 5G sales in 2024 and are rapidly layering AI capabilities — while the software-orchestration and managed-services layer is more fragmented, with Amdocs, Cisco, IBM, and cloud hyperscalers each occupying distinct niches. www.mckinsey.com A structural inflection point occurred in May 2025 when AWS withdrew its dedicated private 5G offering, consolidating the cloud-native route around Microsoft Azure Private MEC and Nokia's joint 5G Industrial Edge with AWS. omdia.tech.informa.com Amdocs occupies a strategically differentiated position as a telco-software integrator and managed-services enabler: it does not build RAN hardware, but its patent portfolio (119 patents, heavily weighted to H04L/H04W orchestration and AI-managed network analytics) and its amAIz GenAI suite position it as the layer connecting private 5G infrastructure to enterprise workflow automation. www.amdocs.com

