## Route Differentiation Analysis

Five primary technology routes define competitive positioning in this convergence:

| Route | Description |
|-------|-------------|
| **R1 — RAN-Native AI** | AI/ML embedded in radio access network (RAN) for autonomous network operations, URLLC optimization, interference management |
| **R2 — Edge Inference & Training** | On-premise/edge-hosted AI model inference and continual training pipelines for industrial workloads |
| **R3 — Network Orchestration + GenAI** | AI-driven orchestration of 5G slices, MEC resources, and policy using LLMs/GenAI for intent-based automation |
| **R4 — Private 5G Federation & Security** | Secure dynamic onboarding, federation between private/public 5G networks, GenAI-based authentication |
| **R5 — Industrial Application Layer** | Domain-specific AI apps (predictive maintenance, visual inspection, digital twin) running over private 5G edge |

